This class manages the dynamic loading of SWRL built-in libraries and the invocation of built-ins in those libraries. A library is identified by a prefix and this prefix is used to find and dynamically load a Java class implementing the built-ins in this library. For example, the core SWRL built-in library is identified by the prefix swrlb; built-ins in this library can then be referred to in SWRL rules using this prefix followed by the built-in name, e.g., swrlb:lessThanOrEqual.

See here for documentation on defining these built-in libraries.
